title: Elipsocus abdominalis
text:
Elipsocus abdominalis is a species of <a href="Psocoptera">Psocoptera</a> from the <a href="Elipsocidae">Elipsocidae</a> family that can be found in <a href="Great%20Britain">Great Britain</a> and <a href="Ireland">Ireland</a>. They are also common in countries like <a href="Austria">Austria</a>, <a href="Benelux">Benelux</a>, <a href="Cyprus">Cyprus</a>, <a href="France">France</a>, <a href="Germany">Germany</a>, <a href="Greece">Greece</a>, <a href="Hungary">Hungary</a>, <a href="Italy">Italy</a>, <a href="Poland">Poland</a>, <a href="Romania">Romania</a>, <a href="Spain">Spain</a>, <a href="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>, and <a href="Scandinavia">Scandinavia</a>. The species are blackish-orange coloured and are similar to <a href="Caecilius%20fuscopterus">Caecilius fuscopterus</a>.
Habitat.
The species feed on <a href="beech">beech</a>, <a href="birch">birch</a>, <a href="Crataegus%20monogyna">hawthorn</a>, <a href="larch">larch</a>, <a href="oak">oak</a> and <a href="yew">yew</a>.
